<BlogPostLayout
  title="Trophies Are Better Than Achievements"
  description="A subjective look at PlayStation trophies versus Xbox achievements: why tiered trophies, Platinums, DLC lists, and profile levels communicate more than Gamerscore ever did."
  category="Spotlight"
  tags={['Retro', 'PlayStation', 'Xbox']}
  publishedDate="Published on May 2, 2026"
  dateIso="2026-05-02"
  ogImage="/img/blog/trophies-vs-achievements.jpg"
>
  <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6 text-gray-300">
    This is a purely subjective opinion piece comparing <strong class="text-violet-400">PlayStation's trophy system</strong> to <strong class="text-violet-400">Xbox achievements</strong>. My overall take is clear from the outset: trophies are the superior implementation, and I walk through several concrete reasons why. It is a short but pointed piece that any achievement hunter or completionist will find relatable.
  </p>

  <figure class="my-10 mx-auto max-w-4xl">
    <img
      src="/img/blog/trophies-vs-achievements.jpg"
      alt="Comparison of PlayStation trophies and Xbox achievements"
